---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

import ContactCTA from "../components/ContactCTA.astro";
import Hero from "../components/Hero.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Mathi Fonseca" description="About Mathi Fonseca">
    <div class="stack gap-20">
        <main class="wrapper about">
            <Hero
                title="About"
                tagline="Thanks for stopping by. Read below to learn more about myself and my background."
            >
                <img
                    width="1553"
                    height="873"
                    src="/assets/at-work.jpg"
                    alt="Mathi Fonseca at work with a colleague"
                />
            </Hero>

            <section>
                <div class="content bio">
                    <p>
                        I’m Mathi, a Principal Solutions Architect specialising
                        in payments, based in Berlin.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        My career started with headphones always on, building
                        whatever the ticket said. Over time I became the one
                        writing the tickets — and eventually the one talking
                        about tickets that haven’t been written yet. I’ve been
                        an engineer, a manager, an architect, a travelling
                        salesman, and a founding employee, sometimes all at
                        once.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Outside of payments: stoicism, teaching, beer, and being
                        the only Uruguayan that doesn’t play football.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section>
                <h2 class="section-title">Building & Leadership</h2>
                <div class="content">
                    <p>
                        Although I started my career as a headphones-always-on
                        coder, the startup fast-paced mindset taught me that
                        understanding the broader business and product context
                        was essential. Over time, I took on responsibilities
                        beyond pure technical work, including aligning with
                        business interests, collaborating with product and data
                        teams, and even working with sales teams. This holistic
                        approach has allowed me to better understand user needs,
                        prioritize development efforts, and drive value across
                        both technical and business dimensions.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section>
                <h2 class="section-title">Payments & Fraud</h2>
                <div class="content">
                    <p>
                        My expertise in payments and fraud prevention started as
                        just a project but ended up becoming my main domain.
                        I've integrated 50+ PSP providers, built and integrated
                        fraud prevention systems for some of the highest-risk
                        markets in Latin America, designed a standalone 3DS
                        module from scratch, and designed payment orchestration
                        layers that operate across 50+ countries. Along the way,
                        I've navigated PCI-DSS compliance, strong customer
                        authentication, and the endless nuances of local payment
                        methods — from cash vouchers to mobile wallets. It's a
                        domain where every edge case is a real case, and I've
                        learned to architect for that reality.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section>
                <h2 class="section-title">Architecture & Engineering</h2>
                <div class="content">
                    <p>
                        At Payrails, I designed the core technical architecture
                        from scratch — the blueprint that now underpins how
                        enterprise merchants manage their entire payment stack.
                        At Delivery Hero, I drove architecture across 8
                        specialised fintech teams, establishing RFC-driven
                        decision-making processes and cross-team consistency
                        across 50+ markets. My foundation in distributed
                        systems, event-driven architecture, and domain-driven
                        design has been tested across multiple tech stacks and
                        multiple continents. And yes, I still write code — it’s
                        still one of the most fun parts of the job.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section>
                <h2 class="section-title">Teaching & Mentorship</h2>
                <div class="content">
                    <p>
                        Teaching has always been a driving force in my career.
                        For 7 years, I served as a <strong
                            >Software Architecture</strong
                        > and
                        <strong>Software Engineering in the Cloud</strong> professor
                        at
                        <strong
                            ><a href="https://www.ort.edu.uy" target="_blank"
                                >Universidad ORT Uruguay</a
                            ></strong
                        >, where I had the privilege and challenge of sharing my
                        knowledge with the next generation of engineers. I've
                        also spoken at payments conferences across Europe and
                        US, including PAYMENTSfn. This passion for teaching
                        continues in my professional life, where I conduct
                        workshops, mentor colleagues, and foster growth and
                        knowledge-sharing within my teams. I am committed to
                        creating a culture of continuous learning and helping
                        others develop their skills.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section>
                <h2 class="section-title">Education</h2>
                <div class="content">
                    <p>
                        I hold a <strong
                            >Bachelor of Science in Information Technology</strong
                        >
                        and an advanced specialization in <strong
                            >Big Data and Machine Learning</strong
                        > from <strong
                            ><a href="https://www.ort.edu.uy" target="_blank"
                                >Universidad ORT Uruguay</a
                            ></strong
                        > — a foundation I actively apply in payment analytics, fraud
                        modelling, and data-driven architecture decisions. I also
                        had the honor to be selected to deliver the <a
                            href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iUgQ5mFUBMw"
                            target="_blank">graduation speech</a
                        > at the ceremony held at Teatro Solís.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>
        </main>

        <ContactCTA />
    </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
    .about {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 3.5rem;
    }

    img {
        margin-top: 1.5rem;
        border-radius: 1.5rem;
        box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
    }

    section {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 0.5rem;
        color: var(--gray-200);
    }

    .section-title {
        grid-column-start: 1;
        font-size: var(--text-xl);
        color: var(--gray-0);
    }

    .content {
        grid-column: 2 / 4;
    }

    .bio p {
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        line-height: 1.7;
        font-size: var(--text-lg);
    }

    .content :global(a) {
        text-decoration: 1px solid underline transparent;
        text-underline-offset: 0.25em;
        transition: text-decoration-color var(--theme-transition);
    }

    .content :global(a:hover),
    .content :global(a:focus) {
        text-decoration-color: currentColor;
    }

    @media (min-width: 50em) {
        .about {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 1fr 60% 1fr;
        }

        .about > :global(:first-child) {
            grid-column-start: 2;
        }

        section {
            display: contents;
            font-size: var(--text-lg);
        }
    }
</style>
